    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty bleak outlook. but wouldn't proponents argue that those same provisions actually drive growth? like, isn't the idea that lowering capital gains tax encourages investment which eventually helps everyone through job creation? it seems like there's a whole other side to the economic theory there.",
