      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Proponents of the bill argue that tax cuts incentivize investment, which they claim fuels economic growth and job creation. This theory suggests that a larger pool of capital leads to more businesses expanding and hiring, ultimately benefiting all economic strata. However, critics counter that these benefits are often captured disproportionately by the wealthy, who benefit most directly from the tax breaks. The long-term impact hinges on whether that investment translates into broadly shared prosperity or merely increased private accumulation.",
      "source": "target",
